comments: P vs NP, learned about different ways to think about problems we can't solve.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The class is very interesting. It covers a different flavor of Math. Sometimes Aspnes is confused in class, and the notes this year are not as polished as his other courses. I would recommend spending more time outside class to read on other universities' lecture notes, and come to lecture for the intuition. Homework assignments are manageable but sometimes a bit trivial. Also note that Aspnes doesn't curve. If you don't get 95% you won't get an A.
Fascinating concepts. Would prefer to spend more time on interactive complexity and less on circuits and descriptive complexity.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, if you make sure you get 100% for all assignments and tests, and if you have a strong enough math background.
Enjoyed the topics very much. Great extension on algorithms.
